<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="493" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,760,1454,1926]" pageId="14" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,333,1454,1478]" pageId="14" pageNumber="493">
Diagnosis. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[271,327,1454,1478]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="493">Male</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,241,1487,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,241,1487,1510]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="493">Sinotilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the mesosoma entirely black and the metasoma with some basal segments yellowish red. See the discussion above for other useful characters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,760,1454,1926]" box="[181,390,1582,1606]" pageId="14" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,271,1582,1606]" pageId="14" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,264,1582,1606]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="493">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
